#### 6.3 Organizational Design Principles
**Principle 1 – Separation of Duties**: Critical activities performed by independent business units
- AI Engineers shall not approve production deployments
- Traders shall not modify AI models
- Treasury shall not approve its own reconciliations
- Developers shall not directly access production wallets
- System Administrators shall not authorize financial transactions

**Principle 2 – Accountability**: Every operational activity has clearly identified owner responsible for planning, execution, monitoring, reporting, continuous improvement

**Principle 3 – Independence**: Risk Management, Compliance, Internal Audit remain organizationally independent from Trading Operations and Technology

**Principle 4 – Least Privilege**: Personnel receive minimum system access necessary; access privileges are role-based, periodically reviewed, formally approved, promptly revoked when no longer required

