### Chapter 32. Definition of Market Data

#### 32.1 Definition
- Collection of real-time and historical information describing current and past state of digital asset markets, blockchain networks, liquidity sources, trading venues, supporting infrastructure
- Includes all quantitative and qualitative information required to identify, evaluate, authorize, execute, monitor, settle arbitrage transactions
- Not limited to asset prices; encompasses every measurable factor influencing trading outcomes

#### 32.2 Categories of Market Data
**Price Data**: Last traded price, Best bid/ask price, Mid-market price, OHLC, VWAP, TWAP

**Order Book Data**: Bid levels, Ask levels, Market depth, Spread, Order imbalance, Executable quantity

