### Chapter 81. Enterprise Risk Taxonomy

**81.1 Market Risk**: Market prices move unfavorably before/during execution (price volatility, spread widening, sudden market reversal, correlated movement)

**81.2 Liquidity Risk**: Insufficient liquidity for execution/unwinding without unacceptable market impact (thin order books, low liquidity pools, high slippage, rapid liquidity withdrawals)

**81.3 Technology Risk**: Failures in technology, infrastructure, software (Exchange API outages, RPC node failures, Database failures, Cloud service interruptions, Network latency, Hardware degradation)

**81.4 Smart Contract Risk**: Vulnerabilities/defects affect trade execution/settlement (Independent security audits, Formal verification, Upgradeability mechanisms, Administrative privileges, Known vulnerabilities, Incident history)

**81.5 Oracle Risk**: Price/reference data inaccurate, delayed, manipulated, unavailable (Multiple oracle providers, Confidence scoring, Cross-validation, Fallback mechanisms)

**81.6 Treasury Risk**: Availability, allocation, movement, safeguarding of funds (Insufficient working capital, Wallet concentration, Settlement funding constraints, Liquidity allocation conflicts)

**81.7 Operational Risk**: Inadequate or failed internal processes, people, systems, external events (Incorrect procedures, Human error, Process failures, Vendor failures, Inadequate training)

**81.8 Cybersecurity Risk**: Malicious actions compromise confidentiality, integrity, availability (Unauthorized access, Credential compromise, Malware, DDoS, Insider threats, Supply chain attacks)

**81.9 Regulatory and Compliance Risk**: Failure to comply with laws, regulations, policies, obligations (Jurisdictional restrictions, Sanctions screening, Internal policy compliance, Recordkeeping obligations, Reporting requirements)

